The paper deals with graph classes and their properties, which is a topic commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The concept of rank-width is a well-known measure of graph complexity, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the Erdős-Hajnal property and the chromatic number, which are topics commonly studied in theoretical computer science (cs.TC) and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper introduces a new concept of low rank-width colorings, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category, as low rank approximations are commonly used in machine learning algorithms.
